title.narrative: Task Order #1 under the USAID Asia Learning and M&E Support Indefinite Delivery Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) Contract

description.narrative: (USAID Regional Development Mission-Asia (RDM/A)): The USAID Asia Learning and M&E Support contract provides: 1) a range of technical services to improve the M&E capacity of USAID missions, awardees and other stakeholders; 2) knowledge management and advisory services to inform decision-making and strengthen development programming; (3) capacity building for collaboration, learning and adapting within USAID missions; and (4) the technical and management capacity building of local and regional M&E partners..In addition to providing all requested services from USAID missions, this task order organizes a biennial M&E summit and maintains two rosters for USAID: one of M&E consultants, and another one of vetted Asian local and regional M&E organizations with the potential to provide services directly to USAID to increase the pool of M&E service providers in the region. The costs for this task order are shared between RDMA and bilateral missions that use its services..
